    "Lee et al. (2020) introduced BioBERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers for Biomedical Text Mining) based on BERT.",
    "This transformer was trained on PubMed abstracts and PMC full-text articles.",
    "Beltagy et al. (2019) re-trained BERT using biomedical data from Semantic Scholar to create SciBERT.",
    "The training corpus included 1.14 million full papers.",
    "Lastly, Carrino et al. (2021) trained a transformerbased system for Spanish using data from Scielo, Wikipedia, patents, EMEA, and PubMed, among others."
